olive oil
1 Brown Onion
1 packet beef strips
1 cucumber
1 tsp honey
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 sachet Berbere seasoning

• Thinly slice onion.
• Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons.

• In a medium bowl, combine Berbere seasoning, a drizzle of olive oil and a
pinch of salt. Season with pepper, then add beef strips. Toss to coat and
set aside.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook onion
until just tender, 2-3 minutes.
• Add beef strips and cook, tossing, until browned and cooked through,
1-2 minutes.
• Remove from heat, then add the honey, tossing beef to coat. Set aside.
• Meanwhile, microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts,
until warmed through.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• In a medium bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, dill & parsley
mayonnaise and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• Fill tortillas with some creamy slaw and cucumber.
• Top with shawarma-style beef and onion to serve. Enjoy!